1. Create a directory
mkdir -p ~/terraform/capstone/1

2. Clone https://github.com/Infrastructure Capstone/capstone.git

3. Switch to cd ~/terraform/Infrastructure Capstone/1 and then execute 

terraform plan 

to verify resources related to VPC, public subnet, IG, SG, IAM Role, Policy

4. Then execute 

terraform apply

As an outcome you will see an EC2 instance with public access with Terraform binary installed and necessary admin rights .
